\layout Title

Autoadaptation with real-valued genes
\layout Author

Marko Grönroos
\layout Abstract

This document describes a study of autoadaptation with NeHeP evolutinary
 library.
 The system evolves a population of individuals with floating-point genes
 in an environment which changes periodically, so the population has to
 re-adapt to the new environment.
 The real-valued genes have their mutation rates encoded in the genotype,
 so the mutation rates are also evolved.
\layout Section

Introduction
\layout Standard

The autoadaptation methods used in this study are based on methods presented
 by Thomas Bäck.
\layout Standard

Autoadaptation is useful for two purposes.
 First, it helps an evolutionary system to find good parameters for itself
 at different times during evolution.
 Second, it helps find optimal evolutionary parameters when the environment
 changes.
\layout Standard

We use the 
\noun on 
NeHeP
\noun default 
 evolutionary algorithm library to conduct these tests.
